Real Madrid manager, Zinedine Zidane, has released a 21-man squad to tackle Shakhtar Donetsk in the Champions League on Tuesday evening. The Frenchman omitted forward Eden Hazard from the squad to face Shakhtar Donetsk due to injury. Zidane released the list in a post via the club’s official website. Zidane’s men head to the game after losing 2-1 to Alaves in the La Liga over the weekend. Real Madrid’s squad against Shakhtar Donetsk: Goalkeepers: Courtois, Lunin and Altube. Defenders: E. Militão, R. Varane, Nacho, Marcelo, F. Mendy and Chust. Midfielders: Kroos, Modrić, Casemiro, Ødegaard, Isco and Arribas. Strikers: Benzema, Asensio, Lucas V., Vini Jr., Mariano and Rodrygo The kick-off time for the game is 6:55 pm.